- store and store8 should be c@ and c! to avoid confusion
- with that step i should also reduce the mapping overhead, it should be 1:1

errors / warnings:
- no main
- conflicting alloc/const/def names
- undefined function or variable reference
- $include file not found
- circular includes
- $alloc cursor reaching param region (0x4000) or stack region
- $section pointing into code region (heap overwrites code)
- $section going backwards over a previous $alloc (silent overwrite)
- string literals pushing code region into the $section range
- deref on a non-ptr type
- if branches with mismatched types
- while condition not bool
- [det] function laundering effects via addr+execute of a [nondet] function
- extern / const / $alloc declared but never used (warning)

optimizations:
- sub-expression constfold: fold det calls with constant args anywhere they appear, not just inside det functions — the containing function's effect is irrelevant
- auto-decomposition: identify det sub-regions inside nondet/semidet functions, extract them into separate det functions with their free variables as explicit parameters; or at minimum warn that a large det sub-expression exists and could be extracted

the point of the type system is to compile time check before running the kernel, since the mce is threaded im using the same thread as the kernel is doing, so i cant leave anything on there

